  "prompt": "How has the profession of nursing changed in the past century?",
  "response": "The nursing profession has undergone significant changes over the past century:\n\n1. Education\n- Shifted from hospital-based training to college and university degree programs\n- Expanded academic requirements and specialization opportunities\n- Increased focus on scientific and evidence-based practice\n\n2. Professional Status\n- Gained greater professional recognition and autonomy\n- Expanded roles in healthcare decision-making\n- Developed specialized certifications and advanced practice roles\n\n3. Technology\n- Integrated advanced medical technologies and digital health systems\n- Expanded use of electronic medical records\n- Developed more sophisticated medical equipment and diagnostic tools\n\n4. Diversity and Representation\n- Increased gender and racial diversity in the profession\n- More opportunities for men in nursing\n- Greater representation of minority groups\n\n5. Scope of Practice\n- Expanded clinical responsibilities\n- Advanced practice roles like nurse practitioners\n- Greater involvement in primary and specialized healthcare\n\n6. Patient Care Approach\n- Shifted towards more holistic, patient-centered care\n- Increased emphasis on mental health and emotional support\n- More collaborative and interdisciplinary healthcare models\n\n7. Global Health\n- Greater involvement in public health initiatives\n- More international humanitarian nursing opportunities\n- Enhanced focus on global health challenges\n\nThese changes reflect broader societal, technological, and medical advancements throughout the 20th and early 21st centuries.",
